 Yobe state Governor, Mai Mala Buni has declared Monday, and Tuesday as public holidays to welcome President Muhammadu Buhari to the state. This was disclosed in a statement by the state Head of Service, Alhaji Garba Bilal, in Damaturu on Sunday. READ ALSO: 16-Year-Old Arrested For ‘Insulting’ Yobe Gov., Mai Mala Buni On Social Media It was revealed that Buhari will be visiting the state to inaugurate projects, including Cargo Airport, Ultra-Modern Market, and Maternal and Child Health Care Complex. Bilal said, “ this is to enable civil servants and the general public to receive the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, Muhammadu Buhari, GCFR, who will be in the state on a one-day State Visit to commission projects.” He, however, said civil servants are to resume work on Wednesday January 11.